      • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

        Good to see Gomez score again. Not sure why he was ever out of the team since the England friendly tbh. I still struggle to see what Goetze offers this team and I think Loew is coming round to my way of thinking. I'm also not sure why Draxler was dropped (unless he was injured?). He is the only player in this German squad who can beat a man, which we saw him do easily today. He has good feet and a deceptively fast first movement past the player. I would really like Arsenal to sign him. I feel Germany will need to be tighter defensively against whoever wins out of Italy & Spain, as well as take the easy chances, but this was much better from Germany.

      • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

        I suspect Slovakia were actually dominated less here than they were against England (in terms of time with the ball) but because they were open (needing to win rather than scrape a draw as in the group stages), it presented Germany with space and ultimately chances. They were poor against Wales and beat a terrible Russia team so you kind of knew if Germany got 1, the flood gates would open. It was only German profligacy which stopped this from being a 6-0. Oezil is a poor penalty taker and I knew he would miss. Ditto when he had the chance later on in the first half. So much of his game is natural, but he needs to work on finishing. If he adds goalscoring to his game then he could be a genuine all-time great #10. As it is, whenever I see him on the end of the chance, I'm thinking "he'll miss".

        One of the most dominative performance so far in Euros. A level difference between these teams was huge.
